        "client_msg_id": "18f31608-78e4-44af-ba0b-f457cd40c6ca",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "Good process <@UUVRX9C13>.\n\nI do feel that if you're hiring someone in a strategic position then you'll want to test their ability to think strategically <@UJG4WTGKS>.\n\nI was previously asked to help a company with hiring a marketing manager and what we did was to share the biggest marketing challenge the company was facing at the time with the candidate, and then ask them to put together a short  presentation going through:\n\n1) 1-3 things they feel aren't working for the company right now, and\n\n2) 3 things we can do to achieve the desired outcome (or improve the situation) within the next 90 days.\n\nThis tests both strategic thinking and the ability to communicate a clear plan to the team.\n\nWorth noting here that the practical exercise only happened after they passed through an initial group interview round with several team members to determine culture fit.",
